{"title":"SDG Drops New Tellis V2 Dropper Post With Better Features and Easy Serviceability","link":"https://bikerumor.com/sdg-tellis-v2-dropper-post/","date":1712752320000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" alt=\"(Photos/SDG)\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://sdgcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Speed Defies Gravity</a> (SDG), the small, independent Southern California brand launches its new Tellis V2<a href=\"https://sdgcomponents.com/products/tellis-v2-dropper-post\" target=\"_blank\"> Dropper Post</a>. The posts are available now, or you can find the new post spec’d on some big players in the game, like Transition, Santa Cruz, Pivot, Divinci, Cube, and YT.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-shralp.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"852\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-shralp.jpeg\" alt=\"SDG Tellis V2 Dropper Post shralp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-shralp.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-shralp-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-shralp-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-shralp-768x511.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-shralp-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-shralp-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/SDG)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The market has evolved since the release of the original Tellis back in 2018. And SDG says it’s listened, learned, tested, and refined to keep this new post on top. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-tightening-easy-access-bolts.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-tightening-easy-access-bolts.jpeg\" alt=\"SDG Tellis V2 Dropper Post tightening easy access bolts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-tightening-easy-access-bolts.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-tightening-easy-access-bolts-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-tightening-easy-access-bolts-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-tightening-easy-access-bolts-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-tightening-easy-access-bolts-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-tightening-easy-access-bolts-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new version of the Tellis V2 Dropper Post features a new patent-pending low stack height head which is 10mm lower than the OG Telliis. The newer version also has side bolts that are easier to access. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-unique-low-stack-head.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-unique-low-stack-head.jpeg\" alt=\"SDG Tellis V2 Dropper Post unique low stack head\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-easy-access-side-bolts.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-easy-access-side-bolts.jpeg\" alt=\"SDG Tellis V2 Dropper Post easy access side bolts\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 3D forged head, which is part of the I-Beam cardle design, combines a stronger 26mm stanchion. This helps improve stiffness. It also provides overall durability and reduces overlap. The new Tellis V2 is available in 30.9, 31.6, and 34.9mm diameters. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-slammed-bro.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-slammed-bro.jpeg\" alt=\"SDG Tellis V2 Dropper Post slammed bro\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-slammed-bro.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-slammed-bro-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-slammed-bro-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-slammed-bro-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-slammed-bro-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-slammed-bro-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The V2 provides one of the largest dropper travel ranges in the game – 55mm to 230mm. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The updated and improved polycarbonate keyway system now includes lower copper shims to further increase durability. This also helps with keeping the head play at bay, while still retaining its smooth stroke feel. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, offering the rider the option to reduce travel heights to help with fitment, the new simple-to-use travel adjustment shims are available in 5, 10, or 20mm, and are included with every Tellis V2. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Durability and Ease of Service</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-Bottom-of-cartridge.jpeg\"><img width=\"853\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-Bottom-of-cartridge.jpeg\" alt=\"SDG Tellis V2 Dropper Post Bottom of cartridge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-Bottom-of-cartridge.jpeg 853w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-Bottom-of-cartridge-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-Bottom-of-cartridge-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-Bottom-of-cartridge-768x1152.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-cartridge.jpeg\"><img width=\"853\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-cartridge.jpeg\" alt=\"SDG Tellis V2 Dropper Post cartridge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-cartridge.jpeg 853w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-cartridge-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-cartridge-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-cartridge-768x1152.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-internal.jpeg\"><img width=\"720\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-internal.jpeg\" alt=\"SDG Tellis V2 Dropper Post internal\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-internal.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-internal-169x300.jpeg 169w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/SDG-Tellis-V2-Dropper-Post-internal-68x120.jpeg 68w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Durability was the foundation on which Tellis was designed. With IGUS bushings, a sealed Wintek cartridge and Trelleborg main seal, the Trellis virtually does away with maintenance problems that other posts experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you decide to give your new Trellis V2 some attention, the V2 is designed to be easily serviceable at home. with no proprietary tools. The entire post can be “removed and torn down in under 5 minutes, even by the most inexperienced of mechanics and at no cost.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To make things even easier, SDG provides a collection of step-by-step maintenance and service procedure videos on their <a href=\"https://sdgcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">website</a>, as well as their <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@SDGCOMPONENTS\" target=\"_blank\">YouTube Channel</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tellis V2 Highlights</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>New Patent-pending low stack height head </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Side access bolts are easy to get to, allowing for quick, on-the-fly saddle adjustments</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The new 5mm reduced height actuator provides improved overall fitment</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Easy to maintain</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: Starting at $199</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tellisd V2 is available now worldwide and includes a limited lifetime warranty. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://sdgcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">SDGComponents.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sdg-tellis-v2-dropper-post/\">SDG Drops New Tellis V2 Dropper Post With Better Features and Easy Serviceability</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8ebc7ac249fb15a2499cdaa41ed9cd2c119870ca7704534172b662c5f799054f","category":"Cycling"}